  fhir:description [ fhir:v "Tumour grade and differentiation codes aligned with the CanReg5 ICD-O-3.2 grade dictionary. Codes 1-4 represent histological grade (well differentiated to undifferentiated/anaplastic). Codes 5-8 are reserved for lymphomas and leukaemias (T-cell, B-cell, Null cell, NK cell). Code 9 represents unknown/not stated. Grade is mandatory only when behaviour is malignant (3). These codes are used in the Grade data quality check."] ; # 
